# Design Library Rule (Tailwind UI reference)

The reference component library lives at [design/application-ui/](mdc:design/application-ui/).

## Critical: Copy, donâ€™t import

- Do NOT import from `design/application-ui/`.
- Instead:
  1. Find an appropriate component by file path, file name and `@tags`.
  2. Open the file and confirm it matches the use case.
  3. Copy the raw JSX.
  4. Paste into your `src/` component or route and adapt to TypeScript/Next.js as needed.

## File discovery and naming

- Files follow `[category]/[variant].jsx`. Use prompt keywords to match filenames.
- Examples:
  - Settings screen (stacked): [design/application-ui/page-examples/settings-screens/stacked.jsx](mdc:design/application-ui/page-examples/settings-screens/stacked.jsx)
  - Sidebar shell: [design/application-ui/application-shells/sidebar/sidebar-with-header.jsx](mdc:design/application-ui/application-shells/sidebar/sidebar-with-header.jsx)
  - Modal dialog: [design/application-ui/overlays/modal-dialogs/simple-alert-with-left-aligned-buttons.jsx](mdc:design/application-ui/overlays/modal-dialogs/simple-alert-with-left-aligned-buttons.jsx)

## Adapting copied JSX

- Convert to TSX: type component props, remove any unused imports, and replace placeholder data.
- Use `"use client"` only if the component needs state/effects/refs.
- Replace icons/images with project assets from `src/images/` when appropriate.
- Keep Tailwind classes; adjust brand colors if needed (primary: `indigo`, danger: `rose`, success: `emerald`).
- Ensure accessibility (focus states, `aria-*`, labels, and `alt` text).
